text: I was brought to the famous waterloo street chicken rice , tasty but I feel the chicken rice at bulky batok central is way better

Waterloo Centre is a nice place for makan n dried food.  Loved to eat Indian rojak n dessert. Like to ta pau the big chwee kueh home. There is centre upstairs with many shops selling fresh dried sea food n dried fruits. Can buy small quantity of dried fruits  like 100 grams for trying.

Waterloo Centre is an HDB building with a mix of residential and commercial units. Blocks 262, 263 and 264 are residential, while Block 261 is made up of five storeys of commercial units. There are two food centres and a restaurant within the complex. Other amenities are closeby..

An older shopping centre featuring OG Department Store and numerous small retail outlets.
Just across the well known electronics shopping centre, Sim Lim Square, and located next to the Waterloo Temple
Just an ordinary food court best for lunch especially for those working nearby. Extra long queue for chicken rice shop.
